          <avActivityComment>Over a wide area 15 to 30 cm of snow fell yesterday above approximately 1900 m. &lt;br/&gt; &lt;br/&gt; The fresh snow and the small wind slabs formed during the snowfall can be released by a single winter sport participant. This applies in particular on steep slopes at intermediate and high altitudes, as well as in gullies and bowls, and behind abrupt changes in the terrain. &lt;br/&gt; &lt;br/&gt; Low and intermediate altitudes: In particular on very steep slopes small and medium-sized gliding avalanches and moist snow slides are possible as the penetration by moisture increases.</avActivityComment>
